dataIdInfo.idPurp: Compute the visible areas within a given distance from a project.
dataIdInfo.idAbs: Compute the visible areas within a given distance from a project. Input features can be point, line, or polygon. Allows the user to choose the maximum distance for viewshed analysis (in decimal miles), the number of boundary observer points (for polygons and lines), and the number of interior observer points (for polygons). If the input features are type point, or if the user does not specify a number of boudanry points (for lines), or neither boundary points nor interior points (for polygons), the tool will default to using the feature vertices (or input points) as the observer points. The user also has the option to keep the interim data (buffer, DEM clip, and boundary/interior observer points); if not selected, the tool will return only the final Observer_Points feature class, Viewshed raster and Viewshed_Polygons feature class.
